The paper discusses optimization problems in the context of propositional constraints, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The focus on complexity analysis suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC), while the consideration of families of representations for objective functions suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
